{"type":"text","timestamp":1775850731947,"sessionID":"ses_2870e4f8cffeSMpqE9zv7zhDn2","part":{"id":"prt_d78f2cb05001anm4ntrWmsR3nK","messageID":"msg_d78f2a9af001Zc4yxNApF00fy3","sessionID":"ses_2870e4f8cffeSMpqE9zv7zhDn2","type":"text","text":"Now I have sufficient understanding of the project. I'll write the proposal.md for AR-010.","time":{"start":1775850731945,"end":1775850731945}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850731999,"sessionID":"ses_2870e4f8cffeSMpqE9zv7zhDn2","part":{"id":"prt_d78f3b9ac001FSxT4JK6905cCB","messageID":"msg_d78f2a9af001Zc4yxNApF00fy3","sessionID":"ses_2870e4f8cffeSMpqE9zv7zhDn2","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-bab7206625294991a19eb9a8d45621a7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md","content":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement session management for the AgentCube Router component. This provides the core session resolution and sandbox creation logic that enables session-aware routing. The session management component:\n\n1. **Session Resolution**: Reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header, looks up existing `SandboxInfo` from the Store when present\n2. **Sandbox Creation**: When session ID is empty, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager HTTP API\n3. **Response Validation**: Parses `CreateSandboxResponse` from Workload Manager and builds in-memory `SandboxInfo` with session metadata\n4. **Store Integration**: Persists sandbox info to Store after successful creation for subsequent session lookups\n5. **Error Handling**: Maps Workload Manager errors to Router-specific error types (NotFound, Timeout, etc.)\n6. **Service Account Auth**: Attaches Kubernetes service account token for in-cluster Workload Manager authentication\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface implementation with GetSandboxBySession, createSandbox logic |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Unit tests for session resolution, sandbox creation, error handling, HTTP client behavior |\n| `pkg/router/doc.go` | SessionManager interface definition, Store interface, Logger interface |\n| `pkg/router/errors.go` | SessionNotFoundError, WorkloadManagerError types with APIStatus implementation |\n| Environment configuration | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required, optional service account token reading |\n| HTTP client setup | Timeout 2m, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 transport configuration |\n\n### Key Components\n\n```\npkg/router/\n├── SessionManager (doc.go)\n│   ├── Interface: GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)\n│   ├── Dependencies: Store (for sandbox lookup/storage), Workload Manager HTTP client\n│   └── Lifecycle: NewSessionManager validates WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, builds HTTP client\n│\n├── sessionManager struct (session_manager.go)\n│   ├── storeClient: Store interface implementation\n│   ├── workloadMgrAddr: Workload Manager service URL\n│   ├── httpClient: *http.Client with HTTP2, 2m timeout, 100 idle conns\n│   └── GetSandboxBySession: sessionID empty → createSandbox, else → store lookup\n│\n├── createSandbox (session_manager.go)\n│   ├── Validate CreateSandboxRequest (kind, namespace, name)\n│   ├── Route by kind: AgentRuntime → /v1/agent-runtime, CodeInterpreter → /v1/code-interpreter\n│   ├── POST JSON request to Workload Manager\n│   ├── Attach Authorization header with SA token if available\n│   ├── Parse CreateSandboxResponse (SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints)\n│   ├── Build SandboxInfo with default expiresAt (30m), status \"Running\"\n│   └── Store to Store via StoreSandbox\n│\n└── Errors (errors.go)\n    ├── SessionNotFoundError: sessionID not found in store → 404\n    ├── WorkloadManagerError: HTTP error from WM → StatusCode + Msg\n    └── readServiceAccountToken: /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n```\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Reverse proxy implementation (covered by AR-009)\n- JWT token generation (covered by AR-009)\n- Concurrency limiting middleware (covered by AR-009)\n- Health endpoint handlers (covered by AR-009)\n- Store implementation details (covered by session-store spec)\n- Workload Manager implementation (covered by AR-006, AR-007)\n- Distributed session cache (Redis-based)\n- Session eviction/cleanup (covered by AR-008 GC)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants (AgentRuntimeKind, CodeInterpreterKind) |\n| `pkg/router/doc.go` | Store interface (GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox), Logger interface |\n| `os.Getenv` | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required at construction |\n| `os.ReadFile` | Service account token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n| `golang.org/x/net/http2` | HTTP2 transport configuration for Workload Manager client |\n| Workload Manager service | POST `/v1/agent-runtime`, `/v1/code-interpreter` endpoints |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `Server.handleInvoke` | Calls GetSandboxBySession to resolve sandbox for proxy routing |\n| `Server.handleHealthReady` | Checks sessionManager nil for readiness probe |\n| Store implementations | Receives StoreSandbox calls after creation |\n| Workload Manager | Receives sandbox creation requests |\n| Reverse proxy | Uses SandboxInfo.EntryPoints for target URL selection |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Session Header Name**: `x-agentcube-session-id` header is client contract; changing requires all clients to update\n- **Workload Manager URL**: Environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` must be set; startup fails if missing\n- **Kind Routing**: `/v1/agent-runtime` and `/v1/code-interpreter` paths are fixed contracts with Workload Manager\n- **Response Schema**: `CreateSandboxResponse` fields (sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints) must be provided\n- **Default Expiry**: 30-minute default `ExpiresAt` affects sandbox lifecycle\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Direct Kubernetes API Lookup\n\n**Approach**: Session manager directly queries Kubernetes API for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRs instead of delegating to Workload Manager.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No intermediate service; direct CR access; simpler architecture |\n| Cons | Router requires K8s client permissions; no sandbox pod endpoint resolution; no entry point mapping |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Workload Manager handles CR creation AND pod endpoint resolution (EntryPoints). Router needs pod addresses for proxying, not just CR status.\n\n### Alternative 2: Session Cache in Router Memory\n\n**Approach**: Cache sandbox info in router process memory without Store dependency.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Zero latency for lookups; no external store dependency |\n| Cons | Lost on router restart; no persistence; cannot share across router instances |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Store provides persistence across router restarts and enables idle timeout detection by GC component. Memory-only cache breaks session continuity.\n\n### Alternative 3: Session ID Embedded in URL Path\n\n**Approach**: Include session ID in URL path like `/v1/sessions/:sessionId/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Session visible in URL; no header dependency |\n| Cons | Breaks logical resource routing (namespace/name pattern); clients must track session IDs; URL pollution |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Header-based session ID (`x-agentcube-session-id`) allows clients to use logical names (namespace/name) while Router handles session state internally. This matches OpenAI-style API design.\n\n### Alternative 4: No Session Creation on Router\n\n**Approach**: Router never creates sandboxes; clients must call Workload Manager directly for session creation.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Router simpler; no Workload Manager client code |\n| Cons | Clients manage session lifecycle; two-step flow (create then invoke); no session abstraction benefit |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Session creation on first invocation (empty session ID) is core AgentCube design—clients use single invoke endpoint, Router handles creation transparently.\n\n### Alternative 5: gRPC for Workload Manager Communication\n\n**Approach**: Use gRPC instead of HTTP for Workload Manager sandbox creation.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Better performance; streaming support; typed contracts |\n| Cons | Requires gRPC service on Workload Manager; incompatible with HTTP-only deployment; adds protobuf dependency |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. HTTP/JSON API aligns with Kubernetes ecosystem and REST API conventions. Both Router and Workload Manager already use HTTP stack (Gin, net/http).\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Workload Manager unavailable | Startup fails with explicit error if WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL missing; HTTP client timeout 2m |\n| Workload Manager returns non-OK | WorkloadManagerError captures status code + body for debugging |\n| Empty SessionID in response | Validation returns error \"empty sessionId in response\" |\n| Store lookup fails | SessionNotFoundError with sessionID in error message |\n| Service account token unavailable | Optional; gracefully skipped if file doesn't exist |\n| Sandbox creation race (duplicate session) | Workload Manager handles deduplication; StoreSandbox may overwrite |\n| HTTP2 connection issues | ConfigureTransport with ReadIdleTimeout, PingTimeout for connection health |\n| Request body unmarshal failure | Error wrapped with context \"failed to parse response\" |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Environment Variables**: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required), reads from `os.Getenv`\n2. **HTTP Client**: Timeout 2 minutes, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 via `http2.ConfigureTransport`\n3. **Service Account Token**: Path `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`, trimmed before use\n4. **Default Namespace**: `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` or from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env\n5. **Request Validation**: `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` checks kind, namespace, name\n6. **Endpoint Routing**: AgentRuntimeKind → `/v1/agent-runtime`, CodeInterpreterKind → `/v1/code-interpreter`\n7. **Default Expiry**: `ExpiresAt = time.Now().Add(30 * time.Minute)` for new sandboxes\n8. **Store Integration**: `StoreSandbox` called after successful creation; store handles persistence\n9. **Error Types**: `SessionNotFoundError`, `WorkloadManagerError` implement `APIStatus` interface\n\n## References\n\n- `session-routing/spec.md` - Full requirement specification\n- `pkg/router/session_manager.go` - Implementation\n- `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` - Test coverage\n- `pkg/router/doc.go` - Interface definitions\n- `pkg/router/errors.go` - Error types\n- `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response\n- `deployment/client-go.md` - Kubernetes client reference\n- `changes/AR-009/proposal.md` - Related Router HTTP reverse proxy proposal"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":26,"character":9},"end":{"line":26,"character":9}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field TLSCert"},{"range":{"start":{"line":27,"character":8},"end":{"line":27,"character":8}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field TLSKey"},{"range":{"start":{"line":29,"character":7},"end":{"line":29,"character":7}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes